<gtr:projectOverview xmlns:gtr="http://gtr.ukri.org/api"><gtr:projectComposition><gtr:collaborations/><gtr:leadResearchOrganisation url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/EC177B1F-35EE-4B74-981D-E8382EE3D18C"><gtr:id>EC177B1F-35EE-4B74-981D-E8382EE3D18C</gtr:id><gtr:name>London School of Economics &amp; Pol Sci</gtr:name><gtr:department>Grantham Research Inst on Climate Change</gtr:department><gtr:address><gtr:line1>Houghton Street</gtr:line1><gtr:line2>Aldwych</gtr:line2><gtr:line4>London</gtr:line4><gtr:postCode>WC2A 2AE</gtr:postCode><gtr:region>London</gtr:region><gtr:country>United Kingdom</gtr:country></gtr:address><gtr:typeInd>RO</gtr:typeInd></gtr:leadResearchOrganisation><gtr:organisationRoles><gtr:organisationRole url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/EC177B1F-35EE-4B74-981D-E8382EE3D18C"><gtr:id>EC177B1F-35EE-4B74-981D-E8382EE3D18C</gtr:id><gtr:name>London School of Economics &amp; Pol Sci</gtr:name><gtr:address><gtr:line1>Houghton Street</gtr:line1><gtr:line2>Aldwych</gtr:line2><gtr:line4>London</gtr:line4><gtr:postCode>WC2A 2AE</gtr:postCode><gtr:region>London</gtr:region><gtr:country>United Kingdom</gtr:country></gtr:address><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>LEAD_RO</gtr:name></gtr:role><gtr:role><gtr:name>FELLOW</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:organisationRole></gtr:organisationRoles><gtr:personRoles><gtr:personRole url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/0389CE29-A9C4-4432-B113-0A1DFF75583D"><gtr:id>0389CE29-A9C4-4432-B113-0A1DFF75583D</gtr:id><gtr:firstName>Antoine</gtr:firstName><gtr:surname>Dechezlepretre</gtr:surname><gtr:orcidId>0000-0003-2477-816X</gtr:orcidId><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>FELLOW</gtr:name></gtr:role><gtr:role><gtr:name>PRINCIPAL_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/projects?ref=ES%2FI015760%2F1"><gtr:id>D3A3BC90-2881-416F-8BEF-CD5BA00B3EE0</gtr:id><gtr:title>Innovation and technology diffusion for climate change mitigation</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/I015760/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>This research deals with the development and the international diffusion of technologies that help mitigating climate change. It relies on a comprehensive patent data set on climate change mitigation technologies, which includes over 500,000 patents filed worldwide since 1978 in 20 technologies with high climate change mitigation potential.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>The project has two main objectives. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The first objective is to examine how technological change can be better directed towards cleaner technologies. An analysis of the drivers of&amp;nbsp; &amp;quot;green&amp;quot; innovation in the car industry will be conducted. Of particular interest is the extent to which these drivers favour combustion motor technology against electric vehicles, leading to technological lock-in. The impact of the European carbon market on green innovation will be investigated. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The second research direction deals with international technology diffusion. According to projections by the International Energy Agency, 97 per cent&amp;nbsp;of the growth in CO2 emissions by 2030 will come from emerging countries. Accelerating technology transfer to these countries is therefore critical. By matching patent data with other country-level data (such as data on environmental regulation), it will be possible to analyse the determinants of the cross-border diffusion of climate-friendly technology, and to explore policy solutions that may boost diffusion. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>

